<HEAD>Thirty-Five Killed In Plane Crash, Afghan Rebels Report</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Afghan government airliner crashed
in the country's southern Helmand province, killing 35 people, a
rebel-controlled news agency said Sunday.
   The Afghan News Agency, which is based in Islamabad, did not say
whether the June 26 crash involved a civilian or military aircraft.
   There was no indpendent confirmation of the crash. Afghanistan's
