three government helicopters during the past week.
   Two were downed near the eastern city of Jalalabad, killing 29
government soldiers being transported to bolster government troops
defending the city from rebel attacks, the news agency reported. The
third helicopter was shot down in the northwestern province of
Badghis, it said.
   The report could not be independently confirmed.
