<HEAD>Three Explosions Rock Belfast City Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELFAST, Northern Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three explosions occurred at
Belfast's Harbor Airport early Monday, leaving two aircraft damaged
but apparently causing no injuries, police said.
   One blast was aboard a parked aircraft and also damaged a second
aircraft nearby, while the two others took place near the air
traffic control tower and on the airfield, said police Sgt. Freddie
Handley.
   No further details were immediately available, Handley said.
   The British province's second commercial airport, situated
alongside Belfast Lough on the capital's north side, operates
domestic flights to mainland Britain and the Irish Republic.
