<FIRST>d a AM-BRF--GuardKilled     07-02 0114</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Guard Killed,0118</SECOND>
<HEAD>Illinois Prison Guard Beaten to Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOLIET, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inmates at Stateville Correctional Center
fatally beat a prison guard with a pipe, a spokesman said Sunday.
All prisoners were later confined to their cells.
   An unspecified number of inmates attacked the guard Saturday
afternoon near the prison's vocational school, said Nic Howell,
spokesman for the Illinois Department of Corrections.
   The guard, Lawrence ``Frank'' Kush Jr., 24, died of head injuries
Sunday night at an area hospital.
   The maximum security prison was locked down indefinitely, meaning
all 2,108 inmates were confined to their cells.
   Howell said the department was investigating which inmates beat
the guard and looking into a motive.
