<FILEID>AP-NR-07-02-89 1802EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-ContinentalFares     07-02 0247</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Continental Fares,0257</SECOND>
<HEAD>Continental Offers $76 One-Way Fare After Holiday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Continental Airlines on Sunday announced $76
one-way fares on U.S. flights for three days following the Fourth of
July holiday. United Airlines said it would match the offer.
   Continental's fare will be offered on all mainland U.S. flights
where seats are available for trips beginning Thursday, Friday or
Saturday, the airline said in a statement.
   Continental said the deal was prompted by anticipated light
business travel because the July 4 holiday Tuesday falls near the
middle of a week.
   United spokesman Joseph Hopkins said the Chicago-based carrier
will match the Continental fare in all competitive markets. United's
commuter airline, United Express, is exempt from the deal, he said.
   Continental's sale fare requires no advance purchase, but tickets
must be bought within 24 hours of making a reservation. Travelers
may return as early as next Sunday or stay longer.
   Continental said in most markets the fare is the lowest offered
in years.
   The airline's lowest advance-purchase fare from Denver to Newark,
N.J., currently is $149, compared to the new $76 fare. Other low
advance-purchase one-way fares are $179 from Miami to San Francisco;
$149 from Houston to Boston; and $169 from Seattle to Atlanta.
   Tickets are nonrefundable and seats limited, Continental said.
The carrier estimated that more than 200,000 seats on its mainland
U.S. system are available for trips starting on the three days.
   Continental has about 1,400 daily departures between 82 U.S.
cities.
</TEXT>
